      <section eId="sec_33_24_4">
        <num>33-24-4</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2745; Code 1868, § 2753; Code 1873, § 2795; Code 1882, § 2795; Civil Code 1895, § 2090; Civil Code 1910, § 2472; Code 1933, § 56-812; Code 1933, § 56-2405, enacted by Ga. L. 1960, p. 289, § 1; Ga. L. 2019, p. 386, § 24/SB 133; Ga. L. 2020, p. 493, § 33/SB 429.)</p>
          <p>The 2019 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2019, deleted former subsection (c), which read: "The measure of an insurable interest in property is the extent to which the insured might be damnified by loss, injury, or impairment of such interest in such property."</p>
          <p>The 2020 amendment,
      effective July 29, 2020, part of an Act to revise, modernize, and correct the Code, substituted "section, the term 'insurable interest'" for "section, 'insurable interest'" in subsection (a).</p>
        </content>
      </section>
